The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 IDBI Fortis Life Insurance has launched its Homesurance Protection Plan. It is a mortgage-reducing term insurance plan that secures the policy holder irrespective of the interest rate fluctuations. The plan also covers properties under construction which ensures the beneficiary gets the full sanctioned amount. The scheme also offers joint life cover where lives of a co-borrower can be covered jointly, saving on premiums.                             
	 ING Vysya has launched a unit-linked saving plan ING Prime Life offering returns on fund allocation charges. For a 15-year policy term, 125 per cent of the initial allocation charges are returned, whereas for a 20-year term, 200 per cent of the fund allocation is returned. It will also offer 5 per cent increase on the base sum assured every year.                            
	 Asset management firm Fidelity has made some changes in its open-ended debt scheme Fidelity Liquid Plus Fund. The name has been changed to Fidelity Ultra Short Term Debt Fund in accordance with Sebis requirements. The fund aims to generate reasonable returns and liquidity through investments in money market and short-term debt instruments.                                                                                                                               
